-- Tesla Opens Trading at $19 After Raising $226 Million in Public Offering
-- JoAnne Norton
-- 2010-06-29T15:27:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/tesla-opens-trading-at-19-after-raising-226-million-in-public-offering.html

          
          
             Tesla Motors Inc., the maker of the
$109,000 electric Roadster, rose on its first day of trading
after its initial public offering. Tesla sold 13.3 million
shares at $17 each yesterday. The shares opened at $19 and
traded at $18.57 as of 11:26 a.m. New York time in Nasdaq Stock
Market composite trading.  
          
          


  


        